===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''[[crier]]'', compare Latin ''[[quiritare]]'' "to raise a plaintive cry", "[[scream]]", "[[shriek]]", perhaps {{F.}} ''[[queri]]'' "to complain"; compare Sanskrit ''cvas'' "to [[pant]]", "[[hiss]]", "[[sigh]]". Compare ''[[quarrel]]'' a brawl, ''[[querulous]]''.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|cr|i|ed}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[shed]] [[tears]]; to [[weep]].
#: ''That sad movie always makes me '''cry'''.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[shout]], [[scream]], [[yell]].
#: ''The captured bear cub tried to '''cry''' out to its mother.''
# {{transitive}} To [[shout]], [[scream]] (words).

